cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC

This paper deals with the analysis and optimization of error floors in LDPC codes, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the application of instanton-based techniques to various channels and decoders, which involves network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of linear programming (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.CC) in constructing codes with reduced error floors.
